WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:09.640
Okay.

00:09.640 --> 00:14.680
If you want to adopt an animal, first we need to know some references.

00:14.680 --> 00:16.240
References?

00:16.240 --> 00:18.240
People we know?

00:18.240 --> 00:20.480
Friends, teachers.

00:20.480 --> 00:22.800
We need to talk to some people about you.

00:22.800 --> 00:27.920
We want to be sure that you're responsible and that you can take good care of an animal.

00:27.920 --> 00:32.360
Then you have to fill out this form about your family background.

00:32.360 --> 00:33.360
Is that it?

00:33.360 --> 00:34.360
No.

00:34.360 --> 00:35.600
There's more.

00:35.600 --> 00:39.200
We need to know about your history with animals.

00:39.200 --> 00:40.880
Have you ever owned an animal?

00:40.880 --> 00:42.440
Yes.

00:42.440 --> 00:44.760
We had a cat when I was eight years old.

00:44.760 --> 00:46.280
I love cats.

00:46.280 --> 00:48.360
Do you have any animals now?

00:48.360 --> 00:50.800
Unfortunately no.

00:50.800 --> 00:51.800
Anything else?

00:51.800 --> 00:55.680
We also like to know your reasons for wanting an animal.

00:55.680 --> 00:58.240
Just to hold it and cuddle with it.

00:58.240 --> 00:59.440
Just to have as a pet.

00:59.440 --> 01:02.840
I love animals.

01:02.840 --> 01:04.200
To have a friend.

01:04.200 --> 01:05.920
A pal.

01:05.920 --> 01:09.640
You know man's best friend is his dog.

01:09.640 --> 01:10.840
And one thing more.

01:10.840 --> 01:12.760
If you're under 21 years of age.

01:12.760 --> 01:13.760
That's me.

01:13.760 --> 01:15.760
Then an adult must sign for you.

01:15.760 --> 01:16.960
Uh oh.

01:16.960 --> 01:18.200
No problem.

01:18.200 --> 01:20.440
My parents will think it's a good idea.

01:20.440 --> 01:21.800
I'll be back with them.

01:21.800 --> 01:25.360
If the real owners don't come to claim gentlemen.

01:25.400 --> 01:26.600
After 48 hours.

01:26.600 --> 01:29.120
But please call first.

01:29.120 --> 01:30.920
Thanks for your information.

01:30.920 --> 01:32.480
And for being so helpful.

01:32.480 --> 01:33.480
It's my pleasure.

01:33.480 --> 01:35.520
Nice talking to both of you.

01:35.520 --> 01:36.520
Thanks again.

01:36.520 --> 01:37.520
Bye.

01:37.520 --> 01:41.760
Maybe the real owners will come to claim her.

01:41.760 --> 01:43.640
Her eyes look so sad.

01:43.640 --> 01:44.960
She must really miss them.

01:44.960 --> 01:47.160
I see you're both animal lovers.

01:47.160 --> 01:48.160
We are.

01:48.160 --> 01:49.520
Goodbye Miss Aborn.

01:49.520 --> 01:50.880
We'll call in a couple of days.

01:50.880 --> 01:51.880
Goodbye.

01:51.880 --> 01:54.120
And thanks for being in genlion.

01:54.120 --> 01:55.120
Bye.

01:55.120 --> 02:06.920
I keep thinking about the dog.

02:06.920 --> 02:10.080
About Gemma alone in the animal shelter.

02:10.080 --> 02:11.560
I know.

02:11.560 --> 02:14.800
But I promise you Alexander, the dog is just fine.

02:14.800 --> 02:17.080
They're very kind to the animals.

02:17.080 --> 02:17.880
I know they are.

02:17.880 --> 02:20.720
I mean about her being alone.

02:20.720 --> 02:22.120
Even if they are kind to Gemma,

02:22.120 --> 02:25.080
she's still alone without her families.

02:25.080 --> 02:26.560
Ready, folks?

02:26.560 --> 02:27.760
Are you ready, Alexander?

02:27.760 --> 02:29.800
Yes, I'm ready.

02:29.800 --> 02:32.360
I'll have the chef's salad, please.

02:32.360 --> 02:36.920
I will have a cheeseburger, medium rare with raw onion,

02:36.920 --> 02:38.760
and french fries, please.

02:38.760 --> 02:40.000
Anything to drink?

02:40.000 --> 02:42.240
A diet cola, please.

02:42.240 --> 02:43.760
Ginger Elle with lots of ice for me.

02:43.760 --> 02:44.480
Thank you.

02:44.480 --> 02:45.280
I've got it.

02:45.280 --> 02:47.760
Thanks.

02:47.760 --> 02:49.800
Aren't you surprised that the animal shelter

02:49.800 --> 02:52.560
is so careful about finding homes for the animals?

02:52.560 --> 02:54.680
No, I'm not.

02:54.680 --> 02:58.520
And a cheeseburger, medium rare with onion and french fries.

02:58.520 --> 03:01.800
And a ginger ale with lots of ice.

03:01.800 --> 03:04.400
Salad dressing?

03:04.400 --> 03:06.560
Hey, I wanted you to hear my new sound system

03:06.560 --> 03:09.240
when the dog scratched on the front door.

03:09.240 --> 03:12.760
Let's finish eating, and then we'll go back to my house.

03:12.760 --> 03:14.440
I want you to hear my new tapes.

03:14.440 --> 03:16.120
I've got some great new dance music.

03:19.800 --> 03:38.240
Hello, Stuart residents.

03:38.240 --> 03:40.200
Hello, is Robbie Stewart there?

03:40.200 --> 03:41.800
This is he, who is this?

03:41.800 --> 03:44.760
This is Linda A. Born from the animal shelter.

03:44.760 --> 03:47.520
It's Linda from the animal shelter.

03:47.520 --> 03:49.640
Yes, Linda, hi.

03:49.640 --> 03:51.520
We have good news, Robbie.

03:51.520 --> 03:52.680
Oh.

03:52.680 --> 03:54.440
The good news is that the leavensons have

03:54.440 --> 03:56.400
come by to pick up the dog.

03:56.400 --> 04:00.240
The bad news is you won't be able to adopt the dog.

04:00.240 --> 04:01.840
That's OK.

04:01.840 --> 04:04.760
Come by one day and look at some of the other dogs.

04:04.760 --> 04:06.640
I'm sure there's one for you.

04:06.640 --> 04:07.600
Thanks, Robbie.

04:07.600 --> 04:11.080
And the leavensons, thank you for bringing their dog to us.

04:11.080 --> 04:12.520
Thanks, Linda.

04:12.520 --> 04:12.880
Bye.

04:20.520 --> 04:23.120
The owner's claimed Gemma.

04:23.120 --> 04:24.760
That's right.

04:24.760 --> 04:27.160
I'm glad for the dog.

04:27.160 --> 04:29.360
I guess I am, too.

04:29.360 --> 04:32.400
She said if I come by, she'll help me find another dog.

04:35.400 --> 04:36.560
Come on, let's dance.

